to the editor final word 'my father 's name was james strom thurmond front page dec 18 quotes edward ball an author and a descendant of a prominent slave owning family as saying the typical case is that the son of a master 's family tested out his sexuality on a vulnerable young woman in the master 's house this is exactly what strom did carrie butler the black maid in mr thurmond 's parents house was at 16 just a girl when she gave birth to mr thurmond 's illegitimate daughter it seems highly doubtful that this test of sexuality was consensual on ms butler 's part we can not overlook the underlying power dynamic that almost certainly defined the relationship between the black girl employed as a maid and the white adult son of her employers mark d harmon belmont calif dec 18 2003

